{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, English speakers learning Azerbaijani may find the language's simpler consonant system easier to master, but they must adjust to the phonetic rules governing vowel harmony and stress patterns.",
    "The comparison of the vowel systems of Azerbaijani and English revealed significant differences in vowel length, quality, and the presence of diphthongs.",
    "Azerbaijani has a relatively simple vowel system with nine vowels, including a clear distinction between front and back vowels.",
    "English, on the other hand, has a more complex vowel system with 12 monophthongs and multiple diphthongs (Flemming, 2009).",
    "Azerbaijani speakers learning English often struggled with differentiating between short and long vowels in English, leading to errors such as confusing \"ship\" and \"sheep.\""
  ]
}